WEBVTT

00:02.170 --> 00:04.004
IN 1979, CONGRESS AUTHORIZED
A FORMATION OF A CONTINGENT

00:04.038 --> 00:07.041
OF ELITE SPECIAL FORCES
SOLDIERS WHO ANSWER ONLY

00:07.075 --> 00:08.642
TO THE PRESIDENT
OF THE UNITED STATES.

00:08.676 --> 00:11.145
THEIR MISSIONS AND
THEIR VERY EXISTENCE

00:11.179 --> 00:12.413
ARE CLOSELY GUARDED SECRETS

00:12.446 --> 00:14.048
PROTECTED BY
THE SOLDIERS THEMSELVES

00:14.082 --> 00:17.085
AND THEIR WIVES WHO POSSESS
SECRETS OF THEIR OWN.

00:17.118 --> 00:18.752
PREVIOUSLY ON THE UNIT...

00:18.786 --> 00:20.888
YOU'RE TELLING ME THAT ANYONE
I MEET ON THE STREET

00:20.921 --> 00:22.523
COULD BE COLLECTING
INFORMATION FOR YOU.

00:22.556 --> 00:24.092
JUST LIKE ANYONE
YOU MEET ON THE STREET

00:24.125 --> 00:26.194
COULD BE COLLECTING
INFORMATION FOR THEM.

00:26.227 --> 00:27.895
YOU MIGHT HAVE TOLD US.

00:27.928 --> 00:28.896
DO I ABORT THE MISSION?

00:28.929 --> 00:31.099
YOU AND I BOTH
KNOW HOW IT WORKS.
WE MANAGE UP.

00:31.132 --> 00:33.067
OUR JOB IS TO PROTECT
THE PEOPLE WE WORK FOR.

00:33.101 --> 00:38.106
AND HERE I THOUGHT
OUR JOB WAS TO PROTECT
THE COUNTRY.

00:38.739 --> 00:39.607
OK. FOOD.

00:39.640 --> 00:42.176
BURGERS AND HOT DOGS.
CHILI--FROM SIGNALS.

00:42.210 --> 00:43.577
ART SPEY JUST LANDED.

00:43.611 --> 00:45.879
THAT TAKES CARE
OF ONE CATEGORY.

00:45.913 --> 00:47.281
LIQUOR
BY ART SPEY.

00:47.315 --> 00:49.016
YOU DOIN'
THE KOREAN EGG ROLLS?

00:49.049 --> 00:51.385
JENNY KIM'S
KOREAN EGG ROLLS.

00:51.419 --> 00:52.953
FOR 400 PEOPLE?

00:52.986 --> 00:54.054
I'VE GOT AN IDEA.

00:54.088 --> 00:56.023
HOW MANY PHONE CARDS
YOU GONNA BUY?

00:56.056 --> 00:56.724
MANY AS WE CAN.

00:56.757 --> 00:58.126
EVERY 10,000 MINUTES
WE BUY,

00:58.159 --> 01:00.228
WE GET A REDUCTION
OF ONE CENT A MINUTE.

01:00.261 --> 01:02.896
FOR YOUR RADIO STATION.

01:02.930 --> 01:04.598
DAMN, THESE ARE GOOD!

01:04.632 --> 01:07.034
"DO YOU KNOW A FAMILY
FORCED TO CHOOSE

01:07.067 --> 01:09.470
"BETWEEN GROCERIES
AND COMMUNICATION?

01:09.503 --> 01:10.338
"WE'RE BUYING PHONE CARDS,

01:10.371 --> 01:12.106
"AND SENDING 'EM
TO THE TROOPS OVERSEAS.

01:12.140 --> 01:14.808
FORT GRIFFITH
OLD HOME WEEK."

01:14.842 --> 01:15.909
GOOD.

01:15.943 --> 01:16.577
WILL THEY RUN IT?

01:16.610 --> 01:18.912
I'M GONNA
SEE THEY RUN IT.

01:18.946 --> 01:21.081
WHAT'S THE DOOR PRIZE?

01:21.115 --> 01:21.882
DOOR PRIZE.

01:21.915 --> 01:22.916
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

01:22.950 --> 01:24.752
GO FOR BLANE...

01:26.420 --> 01:28.456
YEAH.

01:29.089 --> 01:31.392
YEAH. I GOT
ONE STOP TO MAKE.

01:31.425 --> 01:32.393
I'M ON MY WAY OUT.

01:32.426 --> 01:34.828
JENNY KIM'S KOREAN EGG ROLLS.

01:34.862 --> 01:35.996
I'M ALL ABOUT IT.

01:36.029 --> 01:37.498
HOTTER THAN R&R
IN OKINAWA.

01:37.531 --> 01:40.067
WHERE ARE WE GOING
TO FIND A MIXER BIG ENOUGH

01:40.100 --> 01:41.435
TO MAKE 400 EGG ROLLS?

01:41.469 --> 01:42.136
RIGHT HERE.

01:42.170 --> 01:44.104
WIN ONE FOR
THE GIPPER, BABY.

01:44.138 --> 01:45.105
ALL RIGHT.

01:45.139 --> 01:45.973
T-SHIRTS!

01:46.006 --> 01:48.642
OH. DOOR PRIZE.

01:48.676 --> 01:51.679
WHO'S DOING
T-SHIRTS?

02:08.196 --> 02:11.865
CAN I SEE SOME
PHOTO I.D. PLEASE, SIR?

02:17.971 --> 02:20.808
WELCOME BACK TO THE
BASE, SERGEANT MAJOR.

02:20.841 --> 02:23.177
SORRY ABOUT
ALL THE RUCKUS.

02:27.915 --> 02:29.850
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

02:35.989 --> 02:39.393
IT TAKES ALL KINDS.

02:48.402 --> 02:51.672
IT IS THE SECRET OF THE UNIT.

02:51.705 --> 02:54.875
HERE I AM.

02:57.611 --> 03:00.381
ONCE IN, NEVER OUT.

03:01.215 --> 03:03.050
ALL RIGHT.

03:21.935 --> 03:24.405
OFF YOU GO.

03:44.825 --> 03:46.794
THIS YOUR NEW BOY?

03:46.827 --> 03:48.061
THAT'S RIGHT.

03:48.095 --> 03:50.864
IS HE READY TO COME IN?

03:50.898 --> 03:53.133
SO HE SAYS.
ALL RIGHT.

03:54.668 --> 03:55.736
THIS, UH...

03:55.769 --> 03:57.070
THIS OPERATION HERE...

03:57.104 --> 04:00.908
HAS BEEN IN EXISTENCE
SINCE 1963.

04:00.941 --> 04:03.043
ITS CONTROL IS PASSED DOWN

04:03.076 --> 04:05.779
FROM ONE GENERATION
TO THE NEXT.

04:05.813 --> 04:07.247
NO ONE BUT AN INITIATE

04:07.281 --> 04:10.418
HAS OR CAN EVER
ENTER THAT DOOR.

04:10.451 --> 04:11.285
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

04:11.319 --> 04:14.422
IT'S THE TRUEST THING
YOU'LL EVER HEAR.

04:14.455 --> 04:16.223
GO FOR BLANE.

04:16.256 --> 04:18.492
ROGER THAT.

04:18.526 --> 04:22.162
THEY'VE MOVED UP
OUR JUMP-OFF TIME.

04:24.665 --> 04:26.367
WHAT IS THAT?

04:29.770 --> 04:31.505
IT'S A STILL.

04:31.539 --> 04:34.942
IT'S USED
FOR MAKING MOONSHINE.

04:46.119 --> 04:48.689
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

04:54.061 --> 04:56.830
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

05:18.686 --> 05:21.321
[MAN SCREAMING IN ITALIAN]

05:28.061 --> 05:31.098
[GROANING]

05:49.683 --> 05:51.685
[TIRES SCREECHING]

05:58.926 --> 06:01.228
GRAZIE.

