* FIRED UP

06:28.789 --> 06:31.625
6 LETTERS.
STARTS WITH "D."

06:31.659 --> 06:32.593
SEA MAMMAL.

06:32.626 --> 06:33.861
DUGONG.

06:33.894 --> 06:34.762
WHAT?

06:34.795 --> 06:35.563
DUGONG.

06:35.596 --> 06:38.265
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

06:50.778 --> 06:52.412
TAKE A LOOK AT IT.

06:52.446 --> 06:53.581
CALL THE BOSS AT LANGLEY.

06:53.614 --> 06:55.315
HOW'D IT GO,
YOUNG SERGEANT?

06:55.348 --> 06:56.984
I'M NOT GONNA LIE
TO YOU, BOSS.

06:57.017 --> 06:59.553
SHE'S SLICKER
THAN GOOSE SNOT.

06:59.587 --> 07:00.387
THAT'S SLICK INDEED.

07:00.420 --> 07:03.657
WITNESS, THE SEAL
IS UNBROKEN.

07:03.691 --> 07:05.659
DID YOUNG MAC
BEHAVE HIMSELF?

07:05.693 --> 07:08.428
HE WAS ON
HIS BEST BEHAVIOR.

07:08.462 --> 07:09.329
AND WHY IS THAT?

07:09.362 --> 07:11.665
'CAUSE WE'RE WORKING
WITH THE C.I.A.

07:11.699 --> 07:14.301
BOSS, WE'RE
ALL WORKING FOR THE
TAXPAYERS, AREN'T WE?

07:14.334 --> 07:16.470
I MEAN, ISN'T
THAT WHY WE'RE HERE?

07:16.504 --> 07:18.606
AFTER EVERYTHING
IS SAID AND DONE.

07:18.639 --> 07:20.974
SO IT SEEMS.

07:21.008 --> 07:25.946
ALL RIGHT. HERE YOU GO.

07:28.048 --> 07:29.817
ONE, TWO...

07:29.850 --> 07:33.621
HEY, WHAT'S THE CRASH CODE
FOR TODAY IN WASHINGTON?

07:34.287 --> 07:35.489
BUTTERFLY.

07:35.523 --> 07:36.657
WHAT?

07:36.690 --> 07:39.159
BUTTERFLY.

07:42.362 --> 07:45.599
3, 4, 5,

07:45.633 --> 07:49.637
6, 7, 8, 9.

07:49.670 --> 07:52.239
WAAL,
YOU WANTED TO SEE IT.

07:53.173 --> 07:55.876
NOW...HERE IT IS.

07:55.909 --> 07:58.178
THAT'S WHAT 5 MILLION
DOLLARS LOOKS LIKE.

07:58.211 --> 08:01.549
Jonas: THE DIAMONDS ARE
OUR TICKET INTO THE AUCTION.

08:01.582 --> 08:03.617
White: I'LL NEED
YOUR SIGNATURE.

08:03.651 --> 08:04.451
ALL RIGHT.

08:04.484 --> 08:08.321
FULL MISSION.
I'M WICKED COOL.

08:08.355 --> 08:09.456
RED RIDING HOOD,

08:09.489 --> 08:11.959
COMPLETELY TAKEN IN
BY MY DISGUISE.

08:11.992 --> 08:14.528
MAC AND ME HUSTLED
TO GRANDMA'S HOUSE,

08:14.562 --> 08:16.496
BAKED THE OLD LADY
INTO A PIE.

08:16.530 --> 08:18.532
THEN WE DRESS UP
IN HER WEDDING GOWN.

08:18.566 --> 08:21.535
EVEN
I WAS IMPRESSED.

08:21.569 --> 08:23.737
THE CURRENCY OF TERROR.

08:23.771 --> 08:25.405
IF YOU WANT TO BE POETIC.

08:25.438 --> 08:26.807
THAT'S A LOT
OF ENGAGEMENT RINGS.

08:26.840 --> 08:27.675
REAL PRETTY.

08:27.708 --> 08:28.842
IT'S NOT GOING
TO BE SO PRETTY

08:28.876 --> 08:30.544
IF AL QAEDA
AND SHEIKH DASANI

08:30.578 --> 08:31.311
GET THEIR HANDS ON THEM.

08:31.344 --> 08:32.846
WELL, YOU KNOW,
THAT'S TRUE.

08:32.880 --> 08:35.082
WELL, WE'D BETTER
BE CAREFUL THEN.

08:35.115 --> 08:36.684
WHAT DO YOU SAY, TEAM?

08:36.717 --> 08:39.052
HANDS FOR
BEING CAREFUL.

08:39.286 --> 08:43.957
HERE'S THE GREASE THAT'S
GONNA GET YOU GUYS IN.

08:50.598 --> 08:51.899
WHAT YOU GOT THERE?

08:51.932 --> 08:53.601
YOU FOR
OLD HOME WEEK?

08:53.634 --> 08:55.368
YOU BET.
HOW YOU DOING TODAY?

08:55.402 --> 08:56.737
I'M DOING RIGHT
FINE. HOW YOU DOING?

08:56.770 --> 08:59.506
IF I WERE DOING ANY BETTER,
I'D BE ARRESTED.

08:59.539 --> 09:02.342
"BACK IN THE ARMY AGAIN.
SAARTN.

09:02.375 --> 09:03.410
"BACK IN THE ARMY AGAIN.

09:03.443 --> 09:07.347
"TISN'T MY FAULT
IF I DRESS WHEN I HALT.

09:07.380 --> 09:10.618
BACK TO THE ARMY AGAIN."

09:10.651 --> 09:11.685
FOUND IT!

09:11.719 --> 09:13.053
OH, THERE'S THE MIXER!

09:13.086 --> 09:16.556
OH, YEAH.
KNEW THAT WAS GOING
TO GO QUICK.

09:16.590 --> 09:18.692
YOU WANT
TO PUT UP A POSTER?

09:18.726 --> 09:19.459
YOU BET I DO.

09:19.492 --> 09:21.394
WHAT YOU NEED
IT FOR, YOUR PARTY?

09:21.428 --> 09:22.596
WHERE'S THE, UH, PADDLES?

09:22.630 --> 09:25.198
OH, YEAH, YEAH. RIGHT
OVER HERE SOMEWHERE.

09:25.232 --> 09:30.771
IT'S GOT--IT COMES WITH THE
PADDLE, A COUPLE OF PADDLES.

09:30.804 --> 09:33.140
MAKING EGG ROLLS.

09:33.173 --> 09:36.543
JENNY KIM'S
KOREAN EGG ROLLS.

09:36.576 --> 09:37.410
HOT AS SIN.

09:37.444 --> 09:38.345
GONNA HAVE A BAND.

09:38.378 --> 09:43.050
YEAH, BUT I MEANT WHAT'S
THE MONEY GOING FOR?

09:43.083 --> 09:44.985
PHONE CARDS.

09:45.018 --> 09:45.986
PHONE CARDS?

09:46.019 --> 09:50.257
ANYONE FROM FORT GRIFFITH
ON DEPLOYMENT IN IRAQ,

09:50.290 --> 09:52.660
WE'RE GIVING THEM
FREE PHONE CARDS.

09:52.693 --> 09:55.595
WELL, THAT'S
A GOOD IDEA.

09:55.629 --> 09:57.397
CALL HOME.

09:57.430 --> 09:58.799
YOU BET.

09:58.832 --> 10:00.467
PHONE CARDS FREE?

10:00.500 --> 10:02.602
AS MUCH AS WE CAN BUY,
ALL FREE.

10:02.636 --> 10:06.173
AND I'VE BEEN TOLD
THAT WE MIGHT HAVE SOME

10:06.206 --> 10:09.342
UNACCUSTOMED LIQUOR THERE.

10:09.376 --> 10:10.477
MOONSHINE.

10:10.510 --> 10:11.411
WELL, NOW...

10:11.444 --> 10:12.445
YOU NEVER KNOW.

10:12.479 --> 10:15.315
WHAT YOU GOT
FOR A DOOR PRIZE?

10:15.348 --> 10:16.116
WHAT?

10:16.149 --> 10:18.085
WHAT'S THE DOOR PRIZE?

10:18.118 --> 10:19.619
YOU WANNA MAKE MONEY,

10:19.653 --> 10:25.492
THE BEST WAY TO MAKE MONEY
IS A DOOR PRIZE.

10:32.499 --> 10:33.801
Protestors: BRING THEM HOME!

10:33.834 --> 10:35.535
BRING THEM HOME!
NO MORE WAR!

10:35.568 --> 10:38.371
[OVERLAPPING SHOUTING
AND CHANTING]

10:51.351 --> 10:55.355
Protestors: WE WANT FREEDOM!
WE WANT FREEDOM!

10:55.388 --> 10:58.491
WE WANT FREEDOM!
WE WANT FREEDOM!

10:58.525 --> 11:02.295
WE WANT FREEDOM!
WE WANT FREEDOM!

11:02.329 --> 11:04.031
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

11:04.064 --> 11:05.899
NO. NO. YES.

11:05.933 --> 11:08.969
WE GOT THE MIXER, BUT
LOOK WHAT ELSE WE GOT.

11:09.002 --> 11:13.907
NO. I WANT YOU TO MEET
ME AND MOLLY DOWN
AT THE MOTOR POOL.

11:13.941 --> 11:15.575
NO. NO,
I'M AT THE GATE.

11:15.608 --> 11:19.246
TAKE ME 5,
10 MINUTES TO GET
THROUGH THE LINE.

11:19.279 --> 11:21.348
Man: ISN'T THAT SOMETHING?

11:21.381 --> 11:22.983
SURE IS.

11:23.016 --> 11:24.384
PIECE OF EQUIPMENT'S
GOTTA BE 60 YEARS OLD,

11:24.417 --> 11:25.919
AND WE'RE
STILL PAYING FOR IT.

11:25.953 --> 11:26.987
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

11:27.020 --> 11:29.923
I MEAN, THAT HOW COULD YOU,
OR I, OR ANY TAXPAYER,

11:29.957 --> 11:31.391
EVER HOPE TO GAIN
ANY KNOWLEDGE,

11:31.424 --> 11:33.861
LET ALONE CONTROL, OVER WHAT
GOES ON IN THE MILITARY.

11:33.894 --> 11:38.431
TAXPAYERS
PROBABLY PAID $300
FOR THAT JEEP IN 1943,

11:38.465 --> 11:40.100
AND WE'RE STILL CARRYING
IT ON OUR BOOKS.

11:40.133 --> 11:42.202
MAKES YOU WONDER
WHAT WE'RE DOING HERE.

11:42.235 --> 11:48.041
I MEAN, WE'RE CHANGING
SLOGANS, AND THE WAR GOES ON.

11:48.075 --> 11:49.509
ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MINDS?

11:49.542 --> 11:52.445
WHAT ARE YOU PEOPLE DOING?

11:52.479 --> 11:54.281
THOSE POOR FOOLS.

11:54.314 --> 11:58.418
JUST KEEP FIGHTING
SOMEBODY ELSE'S WAR,
ANY WAR.

11:58.451 --> 11:59.286
ANY WAR AT ALL

11:59.319 --> 12:00.788
DO YOU THINK
THEY LIKE FIGHTING?

12:00.821 --> 12:02.255
I THINK THEY LOVE IT.

12:02.289 --> 12:03.256
LOOK AT 'EM.

12:03.290 --> 12:06.626
ISN'T IT POSSIBLE
THEY'RE PROUD TO SERVE?

12:06.659 --> 12:08.361
WHAT?

12:08.395 --> 12:10.197
YOU'RE COMING TO
THE MEETING, RIGHT?

12:10.230 --> 12:14.401
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!

12:14.434 --> 12:18.705
All: OUT NOW! OUT NOW!
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!

12:18.738 --> 12:21.875
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!

12:21.909 --> 12:25.212
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!

12:25.245 --> 12:27.815
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!

12:27.848 --> 12:30.583
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!
OUT NOW! OUT NOW!

12:30.617 --> 12:33.353
OUT NOW! OUT NOW! OUT!

12:44.031 --> 12:46.099
ALL RIGHT.

12:55.175 --> 12:56.810
WHY AREN'T
THEY BEING SEARCHED?

12:56.844 --> 13:00.480
WE DON'T CARE WHAT
THEY CARRY IN.

13:02.682 --> 13:05.285
WE CARE VERY MUCH
WHAT THEY CARRY OUT.

13:05.318 --> 13:05.986
OH.

13:06.019 --> 13:08.255
CAN'T CARRY
ANYTHING OUT.

13:08.288 --> 13:13.693
I SUPPOSE THEY DO TRY.
DIAMONDS ARE SMALL.

13:14.394 --> 13:16.329
DIAMONDS ARE SMALL.

13:16.363 --> 13:19.032
BUT WE ARE
VERY THOROUGH.

13:20.333 --> 13:22.302
OH, YES, THE RULES
ARE PLAIN

13:22.335 --> 13:25.738
TO THE MEANEST
UNDERSTANDING.

13:26.506 --> 13:27.941
MOVE FORWARD.

13:27.975 --> 13:29.376
ALL METAL IN THE TRAY.

13:29.409 --> 13:32.712
NOW LET US SEE
WHAT YOU HAVE BROUGHT.

13:42.255 --> 13:44.224
YOUR PISTOL
WILL BE RETURNED TO YOU

13:44.257 --> 13:47.560
AT THE COMPLETION
OF YOUR STAY.

13:50.397 --> 13:53.733
YOUR MAN, DOES
HE COME WITH YOU?

13:53.766 --> 13:56.769
HE'S MY ADVISOR.

13:57.670 --> 14:00.207
VERY WELL.

14:10.350 --> 14:11.184
WELL?

14:11.218 --> 14:13.320
RESTORED, STREET-LEGAL,
SHOWROOM FRESH.

14:13.353 --> 14:14.621
ANY MAN-JACK,
THIS MAN'S ARMY,

14:14.654 --> 14:18.191
WOULD FIGHT TO PAY 10
GRAND TO TAKE IT HOME
AND CALL IT "MUFFY."

14:18.225 --> 14:20.860
WELL, ALL HE'D HAVE
TO DO THEN IS RESTORE IT.

14:20.894 --> 14:22.262
THIS MONEY'S
GOING WHERE?

14:22.295 --> 14:25.265
INTO THE KITTY.
OLD HOME WEEK.

14:25.298 --> 14:28.368
PHONE CARDS, FREE
FOR FOLKS IN IRAQ.

14:28.401 --> 14:29.536
HENDERSON!

14:29.569 --> 14:30.703
SAART!

14:30.737 --> 14:32.239
DRAG YOUR IGNORANCE
OVER HERE. YOU'RE
GOING ON A MISSION

14:32.272 --> 14:36.109
LABOR, OF COURSE,
WILL BE COURTESY OF THE
UNITED STATES MILITARY.

14:36.143 --> 14:38.946
OH, MY. OH, MY.

14:38.979 --> 14:40.047
1943.

14:40.080 --> 14:42.049
WELL, NOW, I KNOW
WHAT LOVE IS.

14:42.082 --> 14:45.018
I CAN MISPLACE
THIS FANATIC'S TIMESHEETS.

14:45.052 --> 14:48.221
MATERIALS, HOWEVER,
YOU'RE GONNA NEED...

14:48.255 --> 14:50.423
WHAT WILL THIS COST,
YOUNG SERGEANT?

14:50.457 --> 14:51.724
HARD COSTS?

14:51.758 --> 14:52.892
LISTENING TO YOU.

14:52.926 --> 14:53.793
NEW PAINT.

14:53.826 --> 14:54.427
WE CAN MIX IT.

14:54.461 --> 14:56.463
NO, WE'RE GONNA NEED HERE...

14:56.496 --> 14:59.766
UH...BLOCK'S CRACKED.

14:59.799 --> 15:01.201
UH...OH, MY.

15:01.234 --> 15:03.770
NO. THIS IS GONNA
RUN YOU SOME MONEY.

15:03.803 --> 15:04.837
SARGE, I'M IN LOVE.

15:04.871 --> 15:08.208
I'M GONE TELL YOU WHAT--
YOU COME UP WITH, SAY, UH...

15:08.241 --> 15:09.209
2,500 BUCKS.

15:09.242 --> 15:10.477
2,500 BUCKS?

15:10.510 --> 15:13.413
WHOA, LOOK HERE.

15:14.281 --> 15:16.849
Henderson: OH, MAN.

15:17.150 --> 15:18.218
I KNOW SOME ENTHUSIASTS

15:18.251 --> 15:22.122
GIVE THEIR LEFT ARM
FOR JUST THAT FIRST-AID KIT.

15:23.756 --> 15:27.927
WHOA. HEY, HEY,
CHECK THIS OUT.

15:34.201 --> 15:36.136
MAY I?

15:42.275 --> 15:43.576
"OH, MY DARLING,

15:43.610 --> 15:44.978
"THERE IS A LULL
IN THE SHOOTING,

15:45.012 --> 15:46.613
"AND I AM TAKING
THESE FEW MINUTES

15:46.646 --> 15:48.681
"TO SHARE
THESE THOUGHTS WITH YOU,

15:48.715 --> 15:51.584
"THAT IF IT IS MY TIME,
AND IT MAY BE,

15:51.618 --> 15:56.089
"THAT MY LAST THOUGHT,
IF GOD GRANTS ME THAT MOMENT,

15:56.123 --> 15:58.025
"FOR ONE LAST GOOD-BYE,

15:58.058 --> 16:01.661
"THAT THOUGHT
WILL BE OF YOU,

16:01.694 --> 16:03.496
"MY DARLING MIDGE.

16:03.530 --> 16:07.034
LOVE, JIMMY."

16:09.169 --> 16:12.839
HELLO? THIS IS KIM BROWN.
IS HE THERE?

16:12.872 --> 16:15.675
OLD HOME WEEK.
EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE MEETING

16:15.708 --> 16:18.178
AT MY HOUSE.
TONIGHT. 8:00 P.M.

16:18.211 --> 16:19.146
WHAT?

16:19.179 --> 16:20.147
MY HOUSE.
8:00 P.M.

16:20.180 --> 16:22.482
I MIGHT BE A LITTLE LATE.

16:22.515 --> 16:23.983
GEORGE, KIM BROWN.

16:24.017 --> 16:26.519
LISTEN TO THIS,
LISTEN TO THIS.

16:26.553 --> 16:28.355
HAVE I GOT
AN IDEA FOR YOU.

16:28.388 --> 16:31.558
"THAT MY LAST THOUGHT,
IF GOD GRANTS ME THAT MOMENT

16:31.591 --> 16:38.065
FOR ONE LAST GOOD-BYE,
THAT THOUGHT WILL BE
OF YOU, MY DARLING MIDGE."

16:38.098 --> 16:39.999
"MY LAST THOUGHT
WILL BE OF YOU."

16:40.033 --> 16:41.468
BUT HE NEVER
SENT THE LETTER.

16:41.501 --> 16:42.902
NO, HE DID NOT.

16:42.935 --> 16:45.672
WHICH LEADS US TO BELIEVE...

16:45.705 --> 16:46.706
THAT IS CORRECT.

16:46.739 --> 16:49.576
CONGRATULATIONS, AGAIN,
ON THE PROMOTION, GEORGE.

16:49.609 --> 16:54.247
AND YOU WOULD LIKE ME
TO DO WHAT WITH THIS NEW
FOUND POWER OF MINE?

16:54.281 --> 16:55.182
I'LL WRITE THE COPY.

16:55.215 --> 16:56.816
I WANT YOU TO PROMO
OUR OLD HOME WEEK.

16:56.849 --> 17:01.088
THE IDEA IS: PHONE CARDS
FOR OUR TROOPS OVERSEAS.

17:01.121 --> 17:02.922
WHAT YOU HAVE HERE--

17:02.955 --> 17:04.591
LOOK AT THIS LETTER--

17:04.624 --> 17:07.760
IS A VOICE FROM THE PAST
CALLING HOME.

17:07.794 --> 17:09.696
CALLING TO HIS WIFE.

17:09.729 --> 17:11.064
IT'S A GOOD STORY.

17:11.098 --> 17:13.032
A GOOD STORY?

17:13.066 --> 17:15.102
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
THIS IS A GREAT STORY.

17:15.135 --> 17:18.004
AND WORTH EVERY PENNY
OF THE $3.000

17:18.037 --> 17:19.606
WE NEED KTML
TO CONTRIBUTE

17:19.639 --> 17:21.608
FOR THE RESTORATION
OF THE JEEP.

17:21.641 --> 17:22.575
$3,000.

17:22.609 --> 17:24.111
THINK OF
THE BANG-FOR-YOUR-BUCK.

17:24.144 --> 17:25.712
IT'S A GOOD STORY.
HERE'S THE THING.

17:25.745 --> 17:28.848
I TURN OVER MY PSA TIME
TO YOU, PROMOTE YOUR EVENT.

17:28.881 --> 17:31.718
ESPECIALLY, YOU KNOW,
ONE, MAYBE 2 TWO SPOTS,

17:31.751 --> 17:36.456
WHAT YOU'RE ASKING
AND I DONATE THE $3,000
AND THAT GETS IN THE AIR,

17:36.489 --> 17:38.925
I'M BOMBARDED BY EVERY
SPECIAL INTEREST GROUP

17:38.958 --> 17:40.393
THAT WANTS
TO SAVE STRAY CATS.

17:40.427 --> 17:42.129
I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT
STRAY CATS, SIR.

17:42.162 --> 17:44.231
I'M TALKING ABOUT MEN
AND WOMEN IN COMBAT.

17:44.264 --> 17:46.899
NO, NO. INDEED, INDEED.
I'M NOT DISPUTING THAT.

17:46.933 --> 17:49.035
MY POINT IS THAT
IF I DO THIS FOR YOU,

17:49.068 --> 17:53.072
I STEP OVER THE LINE
FROM PUBLIC SERVICE
TO PROMOTION.

17:53.106 --> 17:55.108
YOUR STORY?
IT'S A GOOD STORY

17:55.142 --> 17:57.977
WHAT IF I MAKE IT
A GREAT STORY?

17:58.010 --> 18:03.116
YOU MAKE IT A GREAT STORY,
YOU COME BACK AND SEE ME.

18:03.983 --> 18:06.486
CONFLICT RESOLUTION
TEACHES US THAT

18:06.519 --> 18:09.756
NOTHING MAY BE RESOLVED,
UNLESS AND UNTIL

18:09.789 --> 18:11.958
EACH SIDE RECOGNIZES
THE ABSOLUTE RIGHT

18:11.991 --> 18:15.928
OF THE OTHER SIDE
TO A POINT OF VIEW.

18:15.962 --> 18:17.797
NOW--THANK YOU
FOR COMING.

18:17.830 --> 18:21.301
IN INTERNATIONAL
RELATIONS,
AS IN CHILDREARING,

18:21.334 --> 18:22.669
2 CHILDREN WILL FIGHT.

18:22.702 --> 18:24.604
WHAT IS THE FIRST THING
ONE MUST DO?

18:24.637 --> 18:26.806
THE FIRST THING.
CHRISTINE.

18:26.839 --> 18:27.940
MAKE THEM
STOP HITTING.

18:27.974 --> 18:29.609
WELL, THAT IS CORRECT.

18:29.642 --> 18:32.645
NOW, WAR--YES.

18:32.679 --> 18:36.849
"NO CONFLICT MAY BE RESOLVED
UNTIL EACH SIDE RECOGNIZES

18:36.883 --> 18:38.418
THE ABSOLUTE RIGHT
OF THE OTHER--"

18:38.451 --> 18:39.152
THAT'S RIGHT.

18:39.186 --> 18:40.920
TO?
TO THEIR POINT OF VIEW

18:40.953 --> 18:42.455
WHAT ABOUT HITLER?

18:42.489 --> 18:44.324
ANYBODY?

18:44.357 --> 18:46.092
THE VERSAILLES TREATY?

18:46.125 --> 18:47.160
EXCELLENT. EXCELLENT.

18:47.194 --> 18:48.961
HAD THE VERSAILLES
TREATY DEALT FAIRLY

18:48.995 --> 18:51.164
WITH A DEFEATED
GERMANY AT THE END
OF WORLD WAR ONE,

18:51.198 --> 18:56.536
COULD THE GERMAN PUBLIC
EVER HAVE BEEN RECEPTIVE
TO THE NAZI PROGRAM?

18:56.569 --> 18:58.705
NOW...YES?

18:58.738 --> 19:00.773
WHAT ABOUT 9/11?

19:00.807 --> 19:02.175
3,000 PEOPLE DIED.

19:02.209 --> 19:04.944
SHOULD WE HAVE RECOGNIZED
THE TERRORISTS' RIGHT
TO KILL THOSE PEOPLE?

19:04.977 --> 19:07.214
BUT THOSE PEOPLE
HAD A GRIEVANCE.

19:07.247 --> 19:09.782
YES, I KNOW THEY
HAD A GRIEVANCE,

19:09.816 --> 19:11.484
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
THAT THEY WERE RIGHT.

19:11.518 --> 19:14.454
SUFFICIENT THAT
THEY WERE WILLING TO
KILL THEIR CHILDREN.

19:14.487 --> 19:15.655
YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:15.688 --> 19:17.790
I DON'T MIND THEM
KILLING THEIR CHILDREN.

19:17.824 --> 19:20.827
I OBJECT TO THEIR
KILLING MY CHILDREN.

19:20.860 --> 19:22.662
SOMEBODY THINKS
I OFFENDED HIM,

19:22.695 --> 19:24.163
I SUPPOSE HE CAN
GIVE ME A CALL.

19:24.197 --> 19:26.132
HE COMES INTO MY HOUSE
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT,

19:26.165 --> 19:29.802
WITH A BUTCHER KNIFE,
I'M GOING TO SHOOT HIM DEAD

19:29.836 --> 19:31.904
BECAUSE I HAVE
A FAMILY TO DEFEND.

19:31.938 --> 19:34.507
IS THIS SO FOREIGN
FROM YOUR WAY OF THINKING?

19:34.541 --> 19:35.908
THE BIBLE SAYS "THOU
SHALT NOT KILL."

19:35.942 --> 19:39.011
YEAH. WELL, I GUESS OUR
OPPONENTS MISSED THAT PART.

19:39.045 --> 19:40.146
WHOSE SIDE ARE YOU ON?

19:40.179 --> 19:42.982
I, UH, I'M
ON THE AMERICAN SIDE.

19:43.015 --> 19:44.517
DIDN'T I SEE YOU
AT THE PEACE PROTEST?

19:44.551 --> 19:46.386
WELL, YEAH. I WAS
DRIVING INTO THE BASE.

19:46.419 --> 19:47.487
YOU WORK AT THE BASE?

19:47.520 --> 19:50.423
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.
AND I HAVE SOMETHING
ELSE TO SAY.

19:50.457 --> 19:53.560
"THE COST OF ARROGANCE
IS PAID IN BLOOD."

19:53.593 --> 19:55.194
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

19:55.228 --> 19:57.664
AND--AND HOW CAN
YOU STAND THERE,

19:57.697 --> 19:58.865
WITH YOUR SUPERIOR WISDOM

19:58.898 --> 20:01.368
AND BERATE THE MEN AND
WOMEN WHO HAVE SWORN

20:01.401 --> 20:04.203
WITH THEIR LIVES
TO DEFEND YOU?

20:04.237 --> 20:05.238
YOU SCREAM AT FIREMEN,

20:05.272 --> 20:06.839
WHEN THEY'RE GOING
TO PUT OUT A FIRE?

20:06.873 --> 20:09.942
DO YOU? WELL,
THERE'S A FIRE, PEOPLE.

20:09.976 --> 20:10.910
YOU'RE AT WAR.

20:10.943 --> 20:13.179
AND THOUGH IT'S HARD
FOR ME TO BELIEVE,

20:13.212 --> 20:14.213
YOU DON'T KNOW IT.

20:14.247 --> 20:15.014
YOU'RE OUT OF ORDER,

20:15.047 --> 20:16.182
AND YOU'RE
IN THE WRONG ROOM!

20:16.215 --> 20:18.785
WHAT ABOUT "RECOGNIZING
THE ABSOLUTE RIGHT
OF THE OTHER?"

20:18.818 --> 20:20.853
THIS IS A PEACE MEETING.

20:20.887 --> 20:21.888
OH, GOOD. WELL.

20:21.921 --> 20:23.256
YOU'RE WILLING
TO FIGHT FOR PEACE.
GOOD FOR YOU.

20:23.290 --> 20:25.258
'CAUSE THAT'S WHAT
THE MEN AND THE WOMEN

20:25.292 --> 20:26.626
ON THE BASE ARE DOING.

20:26.659 --> 20:27.460
GOOD FOR YOU!

20:27.494 --> 20:30.430
NOW, I HAVE
A FEW MORE REMARKS.

20:32.999 --> 20:36.469
THE AUCTION, GENERALLY,
IS CONCLUDED BY 4:00

20:36.503 --> 20:37.804
MR. JOHNSON
HAS ARRANGED A BRIEF

20:37.837 --> 20:40.773
BUT INSTRUCTIVE TOUR
OF THE MINING OPERATION
AFTER THE SETTLEMENT.

20:40.807 --> 20:42.642
THE SHEIKH IS PAID
IN DOLLARS?

20:42.675 --> 20:44.411
AH, YES, "THE SHEIKH."

20:44.444 --> 20:45.612
SETTLEMENT
IS MADE IN DOLLARS.

20:45.645 --> 20:47.880
OUR AUCTION HOUSE
WITHHOLDS 10 PERCENT.

20:47.914 --> 20:51.217
IN ADDITION TO THE PAYMENT
I MADE AT THE GATE.

20:51.250 --> 20:52.552
YOU SEE THESE MEN?

20:52.585 --> 20:56.889
THESE MEN LABOR IN THE
SUN FOR YEARS TO OBTAIN

20:56.923 --> 20:57.957
BUT A FRACTION
OF THE DIAMONDS

20:57.990 --> 21:00.760
YOUR PEOPLE STOLE
IN A QUARTER OF AN HOUR,

21:00.793 --> 21:04.764
WHICH YOU STOLE FROM
ACQUAINTANCES OF MINE.

21:05.765 --> 21:07.900
I REGRET THAT
WE HAVE OFFENDED YOU.

21:07.934 --> 21:11.471
HOW IS SUCH REGRET
TRADITIONALLY EXPRESSED?

21:16.008 --> 21:19.312
YOU'VE THOUGHT AHEAD.
COMMENDABLE.

21:19.346 --> 21:20.580
MM-HMM.

21:20.613 --> 21:24.851
MY FRIENDS MAY STILL
COME LOOKING FOR YOU,
FOR AN EXPLANATION.

21:24.884 --> 21:26.753
I'LL HAVE ONE PREPARED.

21:26.786 --> 21:31.358
AND SHOULD YOU COME
ACROSS ANY MORE STONES
ON A SIMILAR BASIS...

21:31.391 --> 21:32.792
THANK YOU.

21:32.825 --> 21:34.827
QUITE GOOD STONES,
BY THE WAY.

21:34.861 --> 21:35.795
WE SHOULD DO WELL.

21:35.828 --> 21:37.764
WHAT ARE YOU HOPING
TO REALIZE?

21:37.797 --> 21:38.631
5 MILLION DOLLARS.

21:38.665 --> 21:40.833
SHEIKH DASANI
AND HIS ASSOCIATES

21:40.867 --> 21:43.169
HAVE GREAT USE FOR
UNTRACEABLE DIAMONDS.

21:43.202 --> 21:46.138
YOU VERY WELL
MAY GET IT.

21:54.747 --> 21:56.549
[HELICOPTER]

22:34.621 --> 22:37.990
SHEIKH DASANI,
AS ALWAYS, AN HONOR.

22:38.024 --> 22:41.794
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

22:46.799 --> 22:49.602
I REGRET HE IS NOT HERE.

23:05.785 --> 23:06.753
"ITEM ONE."

23:06.786 --> 23:10.790
"PRESENTED AS: ROUGH,
APPROXIMATELY 430 CARATS."

23:10.823 --> 23:13.726
SHOULD YOU CARE TO BID
BY WEIGHT OR BY STONE,

23:13.760 --> 23:17.997
THE FINAL PRICE WILL,
OF COURSE, BE ADJUSTED TO...

23:18.330 --> 23:22.368
LET US SUPPOSE THE WEIGHT,
AND THE FINAL SETTLEMENT WILL,

23:22.401 --> 23:25.438
OF COURSE, REFLECT THE
MUTUALLY DETERMINED VOLUME.

23:25.472 --> 23:29.208
SHALL WE BEGIN, AT, SAY,
4 MILLION DOLLARS?

23:29.241 --> 23:30.710
Man: OVER HERE.

23:30.743 --> 23:31.711
4 MILLION.

23:31.744 --> 23:36.816
4.5. DO I HAVE
AN ADVANCE ON 4.5?

23:36.849 --> 23:38.117
4.3.

23:38.150 --> 23:39.418
Man: 4.3 OVER HERE.

23:39.452 --> 23:42.989
4.3. AN ADVANCE ON 4.3.

23:45.692 --> 23:49.596
Buko: AHH. SEEMS THE AUCTION
HAS DONE WELL FOR YOU.

23:49.629 --> 23:52.665
AHEM. YOU MAY LEAVE YOUR MONEY.
IT WILL BE SAFE HERE.

23:52.699 --> 23:56.402
MR. JOHNSON HAS
ARRANGED FOR A SHORT TOUR
OF THE MINING FACILITY.

23:56.435 --> 23:59.572
WE DO NOT WISH
TO BE IMPOLITE,

23:59.606 --> 24:01.674
BUT, AS OUR BUSINESS
IS COMPLETED,

24:01.708 --> 24:05.512
WE WOULD, WITH RESPECT,
PREFER TO BE ON OUR WAY.

24:05.545 --> 24:07.647
WELL, MR. JOHNSON
HAS REQUESTED,

24:07.680 --> 24:09.081
THAT OUT OF RESPECT
FOR THE SHEIKH,

24:09.115 --> 24:14.320
BEFORE WHOSE DEPARTURE
IT WOULD BE IMPOLITIC
FOR YOU TO TAKE YOUR LEAVE.

24:14.353 --> 24:17.156
DO YOU SEE?

24:17.990 --> 24:21.460
YOU'RE QUITE RIGHT,
I BEG YOUR PARDON.

24:21.494 --> 24:22.629
VERY WELL.

24:22.662 --> 24:24.330
A FEW MINUTES.

24:29.569 --> 24:33.005
WELL, NO, WE'RE
GETTING YOU THE MAN.

24:33.039 --> 24:33.806
George: YEAH.

24:33.840 --> 24:34.941
WE ARE IDENTIFYING HIM.

24:34.974 --> 24:36.676
AND NOW I'M GOING
TO GIVE YOU THE STORY
KTML PRESENTS.

24:36.709 --> 24:39.646
THE MYSTERY SOLDIER AND
HIS FINAL LETTER HOME.

24:39.679 --> 24:41.714
UH-HUH. I DON'T THINK SO.

24:41.748 --> 24:43.449
NO, DON'T
PULL THE OFFER.

24:43.482 --> 24:44.283
NO, NO.

24:44.316 --> 24:46.018
TELL YOU WHAT, I'M
GONNA TELL YOU WHAT,

24:46.052 --> 24:47.453
IN ADDITION
TO THE STORY,

24:47.486 --> 24:50.690
I'M GOING TO
HAVE THE MOTOR
POOLEMBOSS A BRASS
PLATE.

24:50.723 --> 24:52.458
A BRASS PLATE
BRASS PLATE? YES.

24:52.491 --> 24:54.561
"FROM YOUR FRIENDS AT KTML."

24:54.594 --> 24:57.496
YEAH, SWELL.
I DON'T THINK SO

24:57.530 --> 24:58.731
NO, NO, NO, NO.
DON'T PULL THE OFFER.

24:58.765 --> 25:03.570
AND--AND I DIDN'T
WANT TO TELL YOU THIS
UNTIL WE WERE SURE.

25:03.603 --> 25:05.371
NO, NO. NO, NO. NO.

25:05.404 --> 25:06.873
NO, WAIT
TILL I TELL YOU.

25:06.906 --> 25:10.009
I BELIEVE WE CAN
FIND YOU THE WIFE.

25:10.943 --> 25:12.311
THE WIFE. MIDGE.

25:12.344 --> 25:14.313
THE RECIPIENT
OF THE LETTER HOME,

25:14.346 --> 25:16.415
FOUND AND BROUGHT
TO YOU BY KTML.

25:16.448 --> 25:19.485
YOU GONNA BEAT THAT FOR
A HUMAN INTEREST STORY?

25:19.518 --> 25:23.422
YEAH. NO. NO, I THOUGHT
THAT WOULD GET YOU.

25:23.455 --> 25:24.657
ALL RIGHT. THANK YOU.

25:24.691 --> 25:26.092
OH, THIS IS GOOD.

25:26.125 --> 25:27.493
DON'T YOU LOVE THE ARMY?

25:27.526 --> 25:30.763
PHOTO EMULSION ON THE
ORIGINAL, DEGRADATION OF--

25:30.797 --> 25:34.266
DATES THE PHOTO AS BEING
DEVELOPED IN 1944,

25:34.300 --> 25:36.068
CROSS-CHECK
AGAINST THE JEEP.

25:36.102 --> 25:38.237
IF WE ASSUME A)
A STATESIDE PHOTO

25:38.270 --> 25:40.106
OF THE UNIT PASSING
THROUGH CAMP,

25:40.139 --> 25:41.407
SHANKS, 1944,

25:41.440 --> 25:42.174
A MEDIC.

25:42.208 --> 25:44.877
A MEDIC NAMED
JIMMY, JAMES,
JIM,

25:44.911 --> 25:47.179
"KILLED IN ACTION"
PRIOR TO--

25:47.213 --> 25:48.014
PRIOR TO MARCH, 1945.

25:48.047 --> 25:49.916
THAT SHOULD NARROW
YOUR LIST DOWN TO--

25:49.949 --> 25:51.383
YOU'VE GOT
ABOUT 2,200 NAMES.

25:51.417 --> 25:52.952
NO, THAT AIN'T
GONNA DO IT.

25:52.985 --> 25:53.920
WHAT'S THE DEAL?

25:53.953 --> 25:55.254
THEY FOUND THIS OLD JEEP.

25:55.287 --> 25:56.623
LETTER IN IT
FROM SOME GUY,

25:56.656 --> 25:58.224
K.I.A BATTLE
OF THE BULGE.

25:58.257 --> 26:00.426
RADIO STATION'S GONNA PAY,
RECONDITION THE JEEP,

26:00.459 --> 26:02.428
AUCTION IT OFF
FOR OLD HOME WEEK.

26:02.461 --> 26:03.763
THAT'S CHARMING OF THEM.

26:03.796 --> 26:05.598
IN RETURN FOR US
FINDING THIS GUY.

26:05.632 --> 26:07.033
WELL, THEN,
WE BETTER FIND HIM, THEN.

26:07.066 --> 26:11.370
"IF GOD GRANTS ME THAT
MOMENT FOR ONE LAST GOOD-BYE,

26:11.403 --> 26:15.407
THAT THOUGHT WOULD BE
OF YOU, MIDGE."

26:15.441 --> 26:17.777
FELLA KILLED-IN-ACTION,
THE LETTER WRITER?

26:17.810 --> 26:19.578
WE NEED
TO KNOW HIS NAME.

26:19.612 --> 26:21.580
OLD HOME WEEK.

26:21.614 --> 26:23.382
CONTACT HIS WIFE, HIS KIDS,

26:23.415 --> 26:27.954
BRING THEM DOWN HERE
TO AWARD THE JEEP
AS THE DOOR PRIZE.

26:27.987 --> 26:32.058
OUTSTANDING.
GOOD, GOOD, GOOD.

26:32.091 --> 26:33.025
GOOD.

26:33.059 --> 26:37.529
WHAT IN LIFE IS NOT A PUZZLE?
GOSH, I LOVE IT.

26:42.669 --> 26:43.936
I DIDN'T MEAN
TO STARTLE YOU THERE.

26:43.970 --> 26:47.106
THAT'S FINE. I CAN
TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

26:47.139 --> 26:47.940
I SAW THAT.

26:47.974 --> 26:49.208
YOU DID YOURSELF RIGHT
PROUD IN THERE.

26:49.241 --> 26:51.010
"RIGHT PROUD,"
"RIGHT PROUD," LIKE US
MILITARY TYPES MIGHT SAY?

26:51.043 --> 26:54.246
MA'AM, MA'AM,
YOU WON, WHATCHA
COMPLAINING ABOUT?

26:54.280 --> 26:55.414
I WON?

26:55.447 --> 26:57.984
I'D SAY, BY ANY
OBJECTIVE STANDARDS,
YOU WON THE DEBATE.

26:58.017 --> 26:58.685
I DID?

26:58.718 --> 26:59.752
I'D SAY YOU DID.

26:59.786 --> 27:02.621
AND HOW WOULD YOU
CHARACTERIZE THAT VICTORY?

27:02.655 --> 27:03.355
I--

27:03.389 --> 27:04.556
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW WHAT?

27:04.590 --> 27:08.094
YOUR LEAFLET SAYS "THE COST
OF ARROGANCE IS PAID IN BLOOD."

27:08.127 --> 27:11.263
AND I JOKED ABOUT IT.
BUT THAT'S TRUE. AND--

27:11.297 --> 27:12.231
NO, PLEASE

27:12.264 --> 27:14.600
THE ARROGANCE IS YOURS,
AND THE BLOOD IS OURS.

27:14.633 --> 27:15.501
GO ON.

27:15.534 --> 27:17.469
BECAUSE I BELIEVE
IT IS ARROGANT TO THINK

27:17.503 --> 27:18.938
THAT IF OTHER PEOPLE
JUST KNEW HOW WELL

27:18.971 --> 27:23.743
WE THOUGHT OF OURSELVES,
THEY'D STOP TRYING TO KILL US.

27:25.577 --> 27:28.948
WELL. YOU GIVE ME
A MOMENT'S PAUSE.

27:28.981 --> 27:31.350
THEN I'M GLAD I CAME.

27:31.383 --> 27:34.887
I'M GLAD YOU CAME, TOO.

27:35.521 --> 27:36.255
I AM, TOO.

27:36.288 --> 27:38.024
MAYBE WE COULD
CONTINUE THE DEBATE.

27:38.057 --> 27:40.559
I DON'T THINK SO.

27:51.403 --> 27:53.472
THE DEAL, AS ALWAYS:
YOU CAN HAVE IT GOOD,

27:53.505 --> 27:55.742
YOU CAN HAVE IT FAST,
OR YOU CAN HAVE IT TUESDAY.

27:55.775 --> 27:58.077
PICK TWO. WE GOT A BREAKDOWN
OF THE PARTS.

27:58.110 --> 28:01.213
WE NEED TO BRING IT BACK
TO "SHOWROOM FRESH."

28:01.247 --> 28:02.681
THAT'S WHAT
YOU WANT, RIGHT?

28:02.715 --> 28:03.549
THAT IS WHAT WE WANT.

28:03.582 --> 28:05.251
WHAT THE HELL DO YOU
THINK YOU'RE DOING?

28:05.284 --> 28:06.819
I'M TAKING A BREAK, SARGE.

28:06.853 --> 28:07.754
THE HELL YOU ARE.

28:07.787 --> 28:09.221
YOU WILL TAKE A BREAK
WHEN YOU'RE DISCHARGED

28:09.255 --> 28:12.424
FROM THIS SERVICE,
KILLED IN COMBAT,
OR I SAY SO.

28:12.458 --> 28:14.093
WHICHEVER COMES FIRST.

28:14.126 --> 28:15.327
AND P.S.,

28:15.361 --> 28:16.595
THIS SONOFAGUN
YOU BEEN SLEEPING ON

28:16.628 --> 28:19.331
HOLDS THE COMPONENT
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR
THE PAST HALF-HOUR.

28:19.365 --> 28:23.002
HENNY! COME OVER HERE
AND INSTALL THE BENDIX.

28:23.035 --> 28:24.103
I'M TIRED, SAARNT.

28:24.136 --> 28:24.971
HE'S TIRED.

28:25.004 --> 28:27.940
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT
THAT IS THERE, SON?

28:27.974 --> 28:29.041
THAT IS A BULLET HOLE.

28:29.075 --> 28:32.344
THE MEN WHO DROVE
THIS JEEP WERE
GETTING SHOT AT.

28:32.378 --> 28:34.046
THEY DROVE TOWARD FIRE.

28:34.080 --> 28:37.249
TO ADMINISTER AID
TO THEIR COMRADES.

28:37.283 --> 28:40.119
SOME OF YOUR
COMRADES GETTING SHOT
AT NOW, SON.

28:40.152 --> 28:41.120
OVER THE WATER.

28:41.153 --> 28:43.555
WE'RE JUST TRYING
TO HELP THEM OUT.

28:43.589 --> 28:47.493
CAN YOU THINK OF
ANYTHING MORE RATIONAL?

28:51.563 --> 28:53.632
OFF YOU GO.

29:30.302 --> 29:32.304
THE FIELDS THEMSELVES,

29:32.338 --> 29:33.272
WHICH MR. JOHNSON
EXPLOITS,

29:33.305 --> 29:36.242
IN THE ONLY WAY IN WHICH
THEY CAN BE EXPLOITED,

29:36.275 --> 29:37.844
BY NATIVE LABOR.

29:37.877 --> 29:40.479
THE LABOR IS HARD.

29:40.512 --> 29:42.248
THIS SCENE
WHICH YOU WITNESS HERE

29:42.281 --> 29:45.684
MAY HAVE BEEN WITNESSED
2,000 YEARS AGO.

29:45.717 --> 29:49.088
AH. AHEM.
SHEIKH DASANI?

29:49.121 --> 29:52.158
AH, THESE FIELDS
ARE ONE OF 6...

29:52.191 --> 29:55.194
[CONTINUES SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

30:09.241 --> 30:13.913
AS YOU CAN SEE,
THE LABOR...

30:14.380 --> 30:17.683
[MAN SHOUTING
IN NATIVE LANGUAGE]

30:21.320 --> 30:26.192
EVERYONE, DOWN!
STAY DOWN!

30:27.226 --> 30:29.328
OR YOU WILL GET IT NEXT!

30:29.361 --> 30:31.130
GET YOUR
DAMN HEADS DOWN!

30:31.163 --> 30:34.200
[MACHINE GUNFIRE]

30:42.341 --> 30:46.012
KEEP THEIR HEADS DOWN.

30:47.914 --> 30:49.715
[MACHINE GUNFIRE]

31:00.392 --> 31:02.761
GOOD TO SEE YOU, HECTOR.

31:02.794 --> 31:04.530
26. 2-7-5.
BLUEJAY TO SIDESHOW.

31:04.563 --> 31:09.335
BETWEEN BOB AND ME,
WE HAD NOTHING
BUT A NAIL CLIPPER.

31:09.368 --> 31:11.070
SIDESHOW, SIDESHOW.

31:11.103 --> 31:13.973
THIS IS BLUEJAY,
BLUEJAY

31:16.308 --> 31:18.710
BLUEJAY REPORTS
TEST RESULTS POSITIVE.

31:18.744 --> 31:21.247
REPEAT TEST
RESULTS POSITIVE.

31:21.280 --> 31:23.249
THE RABBIT HAS DIED.

31:23.282 --> 31:26.118
REPEAT,
THE RABBIT HAS DIED.

31:32.158 --> 31:35.894
OK. LET'S GET
THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

31:58.150 --> 32:01.120
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.
GO, GO, GO.

32:01.153 --> 32:04.190
WE'RE ABOUT
TO HAVE COMPANY.

32:23.875 --> 32:26.045
THE RABBIT DIED.

32:32.051 --> 32:35.521
OK. HIS BUDDY--
JIMMY'S FRIEND--

32:35.554 --> 32:37.756
WE MADE HIM THROUGH
HIS SERVICE RIBBONS.

32:37.789 --> 32:40.092
THERE HE IS.
SHOULDER FLASH

32:40.126 --> 32:42.428
FROM THE 23rd ARMORED.

32:42.461 --> 32:43.329
MEDIC'S TAB.

32:43.362 --> 32:45.531
ASIA PACIFIC
CAMPAIGN RIBBON.

32:45.564 --> 32:48.134
BRONZE STAR, C.I.B.

32:48.167 --> 32:49.801
TELL THEM.

32:49.835 --> 32:52.438
HERE'S
HIS SERVICE NUMBER.

32:52.471 --> 32:53.305
HERE'S HIS NAME.

32:53.339 --> 32:55.041
HIS NAME'S DWAYNE OSCARSSON,

32:55.074 --> 32:56.442
AND HERE'S HIS PHONE NUMBER

32:56.475 --> 32:58.110
LIVES IN HAWAII.

32:58.144 --> 33:00.046
WHAT TIME
IS IT IN HAWAII?

33:00.079 --> 33:02.381
IF HE'S ALIVE,
HE'S STILL UP.

33:13.992 --> 33:15.227
HELLO?

33:15.261 --> 33:17.496
MR. OSCARSSON?

33:17.529 --> 33:20.066
MR. DWAYNE OSCARSSON?

33:20.099 --> 33:22.368
I'M CALLING
FROM FORT GRIFFITH.

33:22.401 --> 33:26.872
I AM THE CHAIRMAN
OF THE BASE'S FAMILY
READINESS GROUP

33:26.905 --> 33:28.140
OH, DID THEY?

33:28.174 --> 33:30.809
THEY HAD THE SAME THING
IN HIS DAY.

33:30.842 --> 33:32.544
THEY CALLED THEM WHAT?

33:32.578 --> 33:35.381
"ARMY WIVES
SOLIDARITY COMMITTEE."

33:35.414 --> 33:37.216
OH, WAS YOUR WIFE A MEMBER?

33:37.249 --> 33:39.051
HE WAS NEVER MARRIED.

33:39.085 --> 33:44.090
MR. OSCARSSON, I'M
CALLING YOU ABOUT YOUR TIME

33:44.123 --> 33:49.027
IN THE WAR. JANUARY '44,
TO THE END OF THE WAR.

33:49.061 --> 33:56.001
DID YOU HAVE A FRIEND, A
FELLOW MEDIC, NAMED JIMMY?

33:56.034 --> 33:58.036
JIMMY.

33:58.070 --> 34:02.208
BATTLE OF THE BULGE. 1944.

34:02.241 --> 34:04.276
JIMMY HANSON.

34:04.943 --> 34:08.580
YES. I AM SO SORRY.

34:08.614 --> 34:10.015
UM...

34:10.048 --> 34:12.518
WE CAME ACROSS
SOME THINGS OF HIS.

34:12.551 --> 34:15.587
WE CAME ACROSS
A LETTER HE WROTE.

34:15.621 --> 34:16.922
UH-HUH.

34:16.955 --> 34:18.824
TO HIS WIFE.

34:19.891 --> 34:21.827
MARGARET.

34:22.128 --> 34:25.864
MR. OSCARSSON...

34:25.897 --> 34:28.634
IS SHE STILL WITH US?

34:29.968 --> 34:31.870
YES, THANK GOD INDEED.

34:31.903 --> 34:35.641
MR. OSCARSSON,
I'M GOING TO PUT YOU THROUGH

34:35.674 --> 34:36.542
TO SERGEANT CARROLL.

34:36.575 --> 34:39.945
HE'LL TAKE DOWN YOURS
AND HER INFORMATION.

34:39.978 --> 34:41.647
THANK YOU.

34:41.680 --> 34:44.650
MR. OSCARSSON,
THIS IS BOBBY CARROLL.

34:44.683 --> 34:45.551
ALL RIGHT.

34:45.584 --> 34:46.952
THE SAME TO YOU, SIR.

34:46.985 --> 34:48.053
I WONDER
IF I COULD GET

34:48.086 --> 34:50.422
THE FOLLOWING
INFORMATION...

34:50.456 --> 34:56.395
HANSON, JAMES A.
2483956.

34:56.428 --> 34:59.931
MARRIED MARGARET ATKINS.
FEBRUARY, 1943.

34:59.965 --> 35:02.768
MARGARET HANSON,
NEVER REMARRIED.

35:02.801 --> 35:07.973
CURRENTLY RESIDES IN
SACRAMENTO, CALIFORNIA.

35:08.507 --> 35:13.179
HERE IS HER DRIVER'S LICENSE,
AS OF LAST JULY...

35:13.212 --> 35:15.747
AND HERE'S
HER CURRENT PHONE NUMBER.

35:15.781 --> 35:17.916
IS NOTHING SACRED
TO YOU GUYS?

35:17.949 --> 35:19.851
YOU BETTER HOPE NOT.

35:25.857 --> 35:29.928
I KNOW EXACTLY
HOW MANY BOTTLES YOU
HAVE IN THAT CASE.

35:29.961 --> 35:31.697
DON'T HOLD OUT ON ME.

35:32.231 --> 35:33.532
AIN'T THAT GOOD?

35:33.565 --> 35:35.033
MMM.

35:35.066 --> 35:36.368
[CHUCKLES]

35:36.402 --> 35:38.670
THAT'S GOOD.

35:38.704 --> 35:40.372
WHAT, YOU STOP DRINKING?

35:40.406 --> 35:42.341
NO, I WANTED
TO ASK YOU SOMETHING.

35:42.374 --> 35:44.276
WELL, I FIGURED
YOU DID, AS, LATELY,

35:44.310 --> 35:46.312
YOU LOOK LIKE THE DOG DIED.
GO ON, THEN.

35:46.345 --> 35:48.647
THE DIAMONDS THE TEAM
STOLE IN ITALY.

35:48.680 --> 35:49.781
YEAH. I SEEM TO REMEMBER,

35:49.815 --> 35:50.649
WE SOLD THEM
TO THE SHEIKH.

35:50.682 --> 35:53.018
AH, YES, THE SHEIKH.
4.5 MILLION DOLLARS,

35:53.051 --> 35:54.453
9 PACKAGES
OF ROUGH CUT DIAMONDS.

35:54.486 --> 35:57.623
BUT ORIGINALLY
THERE WERE 10 PACKAGES
OF UNCUT DIAMONDS.

35:57.656 --> 35:59.225
YOU KEPT ONE OUT.

35:59.858 --> 36:01.126
THIS ON?

36:01.159 --> 36:02.861
AS YOU RECALL,
ART SPEY HERE

36:02.894 --> 36:06.832
WANTED TO INDUCT
YOU INTO A LITTLE
SECRET OF THE UNIT.

36:06.865 --> 36:07.966
THE STILL

36:07.999 --> 36:10.336
NO. IT AIN'T
EXACTLY THE STILL.

36:10.369 --> 36:12.003
ONCE IN, NEVER OUT.

36:12.037 --> 36:13.472
WELL, HERE I AM.

36:13.505 --> 36:15.341
WHAT'S BEEN GOING
ON HERE, BOB?

36:15.374 --> 36:17.008
SINCE THE BEGINNING.

36:17.042 --> 36:18.076
"THE BEGINNING?"

36:18.109 --> 36:20.712
SINCE THE INCEPTION
OF THE UNIT. IT, UH...

36:20.746 --> 36:21.880
IT DOESN'T HAVE A NAME.

36:21.913 --> 36:24.483
YOU MIGHT THINK OF IT
AS AN ESCAPE HATCH.

36:24.516 --> 36:27.919
SOMETIMES, BABY.
NO FAULT OF YOUR OWN.

36:27.953 --> 36:29.921
YOU, OR ANOTHER GUY.
LIKE YOU.

36:29.955 --> 36:31.857
A UNIT MEMBER
HAS TO DISAPPEAR.

36:31.890 --> 36:33.492
BREAK IT ON DOWN.

36:33.525 --> 36:34.893
YOU REMEMBER
THE BAY OF PIGS?

36:34.926 --> 36:36.262
MM-HMM.

36:36.295 --> 36:37.696
SOMETIMES...

36:37.729 --> 36:40.666
THE GOVERNMENT,
SAY, IT HAS TO DISAVOW

36:40.699 --> 36:43.902
THOSE WHOM IT HAS SENT
TO DO ITS BIDDING.

36:43.935 --> 36:45.203
IT'S HAPPENED
IN THE PAST.

36:45.237 --> 36:49.241
AT TIME THIS MAN
AND HIS FAMILY

36:49.275 --> 36:53.011
HAVE ACCESS
TO FUNDS, FRIENDS,
A NEW IDENTITY.

36:53.044 --> 36:54.513
AND A NEW LIFE.

36:54.546 --> 36:56.282
A UNIT MEMBER
HAS TO DISAPPEAR.

36:56.315 --> 36:57.849
IT'S
HAPPENED BEFORE.

36:57.883 --> 36:59.751
A MAN HAS TO WALK AWAY
AND CAN'T COME BACK.

36:59.785 --> 37:01.019
HOW IS IT PAID FOR?

37:01.052 --> 37:04.723
IT'S FUNDED THROUGH TAXES--

37:04.756 --> 37:08.226
PAID TO THE DEPARTMENT
OF THE TREASURY.

37:08.260 --> 37:11.330
THAT WOULD BE ME.

37:35.020 --> 37:37.756
TESTING, TESTING. 1, 2.

37:38.324 --> 37:39.257
UH, GOOD AFTERNOON.

37:39.291 --> 37:40.626
MY NAME
IS GEORGE TATELMAN.

37:40.659 --> 37:41.993
AND I AM
THE STATION MANAGER

37:42.027 --> 37:45.130
AT RADIO STATION KTML,
"THE MISSILE."

37:45.163 --> 37:47.399
WE AT KTML
ARE VERY PROUD INDEED

37:47.433 --> 37:49.401
TO BE PART OF THE FORT
GRIFFITH COMMUNITY.

37:49.435 --> 37:55.006
AND WE ARE MOST PLEASED
TO BE PARTICIPATING
IN OLD HOME WEEK...

37:56.342 --> 37:58.944
NOW, MR. OSCARSSON.
MISS HANSON.

37:58.977 --> 38:00.746
WHEN WE'RE
READY FOR YOU,
MRS. HANSON,

38:00.779 --> 38:03.114
WE'D LIKE YOU
FOR YOU TO GO UP.

38:03.148 --> 38:05.917
MR. OSCARSSON,
IF YOU'D LIKE TO--

38:05.951 --> 38:08.820
NO. I'M FINE HERE.

38:08.854 --> 38:09.755
MARGARET?

38:09.788 --> 38:13.692
OH, NO, NO. I'M FINE, TOO.

38:13.725 --> 38:16.528
SOME LUCKY PERSON
IS GOING TO BE DRIVING

38:16.562 --> 38:19.264
TO WORK
IN THIS 1943 JEEP,

38:19.297 --> 38:22.634
WHOSE RESTORATION WE
WERE SO PLEASED TO FUND,

38:22.668 --> 38:23.769
OUR RADIO STATION.

38:23.802 --> 38:25.504
COULD I HAVE
A ROUND OF APPLAUSE

38:25.537 --> 38:26.705
FOR THE SERVICE
MEN AND WOMEN

38:26.738 --> 38:29.575
WHO ACTUALLY DID
THE RESTORATION PLEASE?

38:31.577 --> 38:33.044
NOW THIS JEEP
HAS A HISTORY.

38:33.078 --> 38:36.682
IT WAS DRIVEN IN COMBAT
BY SERGEANT JAMES HANSON.

38:36.715 --> 38:39.284
WE HAVE
HIS WIDOW HERE TODAY,

38:39.317 --> 38:42.854
WHO WILL DRAW
THE LUCKY TICKET.

38:45.424 --> 38:47.693
THANK YOU,
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN.

38:47.726 --> 38:49.194
ENJOY OLD HOME WEEK.

38:49.227 --> 38:51.730
AND NOW IT IS
MY HONOR TO INTRODUCE

38:51.763 --> 38:53.665
THE HONORARY CHAIR
OF THIS EVENT,

38:53.699 --> 38:55.867
MRS. THOMAS RYAN.

39:04.075 --> 39:05.010
THANK YOU.

39:05.043 --> 39:08.346
I HAVE BEEN GIVEN THE HONOR
OF AWARDING THE--

39:08.380 --> 39:11.583
OH, THANK YOU, CATHY.
JUST PUT IT RIGHT HERE.

39:11.617 --> 39:16.488
I'VE BEEN GIVEN THE HONOR.
OF AWARDING THE DOOR PRIZE.

39:16.522 --> 39:20.191
ARMY VEHICLE,
GENERAL PURPOSE,
SERIAL NUMBER...

39:20.225 --> 39:21.092
MRS. HANSON?

39:21.126 --> 39:22.861
YES?
ARE YOU READY?

39:22.894 --> 39:23.562
READY FOR WHAT?

39:23.595 --> 39:25.597
IT'S TIME
TO READ THE LETTER.

39:25.631 --> 39:27.433
WHAT LETTER?

39:27.466 --> 39:28.934
THE LETTER
FROM YOUR HUSBAND.

39:28.967 --> 39:32.404
AND THE PARTICULAR HELP
OF GEORGE TATELMAN

39:32.438 --> 39:37.075
AND RADIO STATION KTML
"THE MISSILE"

39:40.812 --> 39:42.013
AFTER
THE JEEP PRESENTATION

39:42.047 --> 39:44.015
JUDITH WILL
TAKE MRS. HANSON
TO HER CAR.

39:44.049 --> 39:48.286
UM, I NEED TO FIND
AN ESCORT WHO CAN
TAKE MR. OSCARRSON TO--

39:48.319 --> 39:50.088
SHE NEVER GOT THE LETTER.

39:50.121 --> 39:50.856
WHAT?

39:50.889 --> 39:52.123
MRS. HANSON
NEVER GOT THE LETTER.

39:52.157 --> 39:53.959
TIFFY GAVE HER
THE LETTER.

39:53.992 --> 39:55.093
SHE SAYS SHE NEVER GOT IT.

39:55.126 --> 39:57.696
WE HAVE A COPY
OF THE LETTER. GIVE HER
THE COPY OF IT.

39:57.729 --> 39:58.830
SHE WON'T READ IT.

39:58.864 --> 40:00.599
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
SHE DOESN'T WANT
TO READ THE LETTER?

40:00.632 --> 40:02.568
WELL, SHE SAYS
SHE NEVER GOT THE LETTER.

40:02.601 --> 40:04.035
WHERE IS TIFFY?

40:04.069 --> 40:04.736
SHE'S SHY.

40:04.770 --> 40:07.305
SHE'S GOT
TO READ THE LETTER.

40:07.673 --> 40:08.540
Wilson: YOU HAVE A LIST.

40:08.574 --> 40:09.875
Tiffy: I HAVE A LIST.

40:09.908 --> 40:13.545
Wilson: OF AREAS
IN WHICH I AM
WOEFULLY MISGUIDED.

40:13.579 --> 40:17.282
ONE. EVERY COUNTRY
IS ONE AND HELD

40:17.315 --> 40:20.786
ONLY BY FORCE OF ARMS.

40:22.588 --> 40:24.422
THANK YOU.

40:27.593 --> 40:29.495
GO ON.

40:29.528 --> 40:30.428
2...

40:30.462 --> 40:32.964
WE ARE HERE TODAY
TO RAISE MONEY

40:32.998 --> 40:35.400
FOR THE PURCHASE
OF PHONE CARDS

40:35.433 --> 40:40.238
TO ALLOW OUR MEN AND WOMEN
OVERSEAS TO STAY IN TOUCH.

40:40.271 --> 40:41.673
HOLD ON, HOLD ON.
WE HAVE A DEAL

40:41.707 --> 40:44.643
DO WE HAVE A DEAL?
I PAID FOR THAT JEEP.

40:44.676 --> 40:45.611
SHE'S 85 YEARS OLD.

40:45.644 --> 40:47.479
I DON'T CARE
HOW OLD SHE IS.

40:47.513 --> 40:48.680
NOW, YOU TOLD ME--

40:48.714 --> 40:51.617
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL READ
THE LETTER.

40:51.650 --> 40:52.818
I'LL READ THE LETTER,

40:52.851 --> 40:55.887
AND SHE CAN STAND UP
AND BOW.

40:56.955 --> 41:00.458
AND WE'RE
PARTICULARLY PRIVILEGED
TO HAVE WITH US TODAY

41:00.492 --> 41:02.861
MRS. MARGARET HANSON,

41:02.894 --> 41:07.999
WHOSE HUSBAND JAMES
SERVED AND FELL

41:08.033 --> 41:09.367
IN DECEMBER, 1944,

41:09.400 --> 41:10.602
IN THE BATTLE
OF THE BULGE.

41:10.636 --> 41:16.007
IN THE MEDICAL UNIT
OF THE 23rd ARMORED
INFANTRY BATTALION.

41:16.041 --> 41:19.511
AND THIS
WAS HIS VEHICLE.

41:21.012 --> 41:22.881
THANK YOU.

41:23.649 --> 41:25.984
WE'RE ALSO PRIVILEGED
TO HAVE WITH US,

41:26.017 --> 41:29.354
DWAYNE OSCARSSON,
HIS COMRADE IN ARMS.

41:29.387 --> 41:30.355
[APPLAUSE]

41:30.388 --> 41:31.156
THANK YOU.

41:31.189 --> 41:34.993
AND I'M SURE YOU
ALL KNOW KIM BROWN.

41:35.026 --> 41:39.330
[APPLAUSE]

41:40.231 --> 41:42.568
THANK YOU, MRS. RYAN.

41:43.201 --> 41:46.237
THANK YOU ALL FOR BEING HERE.

41:47.573 --> 41:50.508
MRS. HANSON, IN THAT JEEP,

41:50.542 --> 41:54.312
FOUND IN THE JEEP,
IN A FIRST AID KIT.

41:54.345 --> 41:58.717
WAS A LETTER WHICH
YOUR HUSBAND WROTE,

41:58.750 --> 42:00.518
AND WHICH
HE NEVER POSTED.

42:00.552 --> 42:03.755
IT WAS HIS LAST
LETTER THAT HE WROTE,

42:03.789 --> 42:08.059
AND I WOULD LIKE
TO READ IT TO YOU.

42:13.632 --> 42:16.267
"OH, MY DARLING.

42:16.301 --> 42:18.870
"THERE IS A LULL
IN THE SHOOTING,

42:18.904 --> 42:20.906
"AND I AM TAKING
THESE FEW MINUTES

42:20.939 --> 42:24.542
"TO SHARE THESE
THOUGHTS WITH YOU.

42:24.576 --> 42:29.447
"THAT IF IT IS MY TIME,

42:29.480 --> 42:32.283
AND IT MAY BE..."

42:33.284 --> 42:34.452
"THAT MY LAST THOUGHT,

42:34.485 --> 42:37.355
"IF GOD GRANTS
ME THAT MOMENT

42:37.388 --> 42:39.357
"FOR ONE LAST GOOD-BYE,

42:39.390 --> 42:43.762
"THAT THOUGHT
WILL BE OF YOU,

42:43.795 --> 42:48.600
MY DARLING MIDGE."

43:02.513 --> 43:05.416
I'M MIDGE.

43:06.484 --> 43:08.419
WHAT?

43:08.920 --> 43:12.023
I'M MIDGE.
